category.name: music
description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.
name: Stockholm Music Industry

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

Let's music2gether!

description:
Welcome to Musicians in Copenhagen.

This group is intended for use for musicians in Copenhagen and surrounding areas.
If you wish to get in contact or arrange meetups with group members, please propose a meetup, and we will make it public, and help you facilitate the arrangement, and perhaps find a place for the meetup to take place.

We keep this group alive to make it possible for the members to make arrangements and meetups. Do not expect us to do the work, it is entirely up to you to make things happen :-)

So if you have an idea for an arrangment to educate or entertain other people, please step forward.

Kind regards,
Per Butschkow

description:
Working with document management, ECM, process management, records management, archives, automation of processes? Then this is for you! We will meet and talk about ECM and related topics.

We'll talk about technologies, best practices, review reports and much more.

All is welcome - both vendors and users.

Don't speak Danish? No problem, we all speak pretty good English!

category.name: music
description:
Indie CPH is a Meetup group for anyone into Indie and alternative music, past, present, and future. We do gig meetups, listening parties, record store crawls, and any other ideas we may come up with.

What's Indie then? Indie is both a label as in "music that is independently produced outside of a major record label", but also a genre associated with bands like Blur, The Strokes, The Libertines, Belle and Sebastian etc. We do like to keep the definition broad, but we're probably not metal, stadium rock, world music, jazz and so on.

So join us and discover new and old indie music, find gig buddies, and join our upcoming events!

We're also on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/groups/IndieCPH/

category.name: music
description:
This is a group for all rock and metal listeners in Copenhagen (and the surroundings), who want to meet other metalheads. Whether you like the riffs in trash metal, fantasy in power metal, paganism in folk metal, growls of death metal or shrieks of black metal you are welcome to join us.

*Please take 2 minutes to read the following, so you can get the best out of this group.

About our group

We are a super easy-going bunch of people – both Danes and internationals – who love to listen to and/or play heavier music (metal, rock, punk and everything in between) and just want to help connect those in Copenhagen & its surroundings with new friends and introduce them to different bands, genres and venues. We love live music, jamming, and going down the pub to chat (with or without drinks: your call). If you haven’t been to one of our events yet, you totally should. We’re not that scary, honest.

Attendance policy

We understand that life happens and things change, but please try and let us know if you’ve signed up to an event but won’t make it. Otherwise we might spend the entire night worrying about you.

Serial offenders will be marked as non-attendees, just so that our hard-working hosts know not to spend too much time waiting for/contacting them.

As Jesus once said: 'Thou shalt not RSVP Yes on Meetup and then stay at home in thine pyjamas watching Netflix without letting me know, or I cannot promise to save thy soul.'

Events

Most of our meetups are created by the organisers, but we strongly encourage all members to be active and suggest events.
You can do so by writing to one of the organisers, or starting a discussion (see group's main page).
So if you’re a concert-freak and always up-to-date with all the metal events in the area, your knowledge will definitely be useful to us!
Or if you decide to go to a concert and would like to meet other people who share your taste in bands, we can create an event for you. In that case, you'll have the responsibility of being a ‘host’. It’s not as hard as it sounds. You just have to choose a meeting place/time and make sure that the attendees are aware of it by writing private messages and/or comments in the event page.

And you can also suggest events in the Facebook group, but mind that not all the people from meetup are members of the FB group, so you'd reach more people by starting a new discussion on meetup.

The Facebook group

Yeah, we have one of those. Find it here: https://www.facebook.com/groups/254082381762001/

We use it to float ideas about possible events, new venues, or just to see if anyone is up for going out or playing some music together. Join it, use it, invite your friends. Interaction is the key to new connections (but remember to stick to the rules…)

Group rules

(TL;DR – Don’t provoke unnecessarily, but also don’t be a massive snowflake.)

This should be self-explanatory to anyone accustomed to conducting themselves in society, but let’s set it out in writing anyway.

Just be excellent to each other. Respect the diverse range of nationalities, personalities and music tastes represented in the group.

Unacceptable behaviour includes, but is not limited to:

Racism, Sexism, Ageism, Classism, Ableism, Genreism, Jism,

Homophobia, Xenophobia

Making people feel in any way uncomfortable

Trolling, Shameless advertising, Causing avoidable arguments, Not taking a joke

NB. Swearing is allowed, otherwise we would have to kick ourselves out of the group, but swearing with the intent of causing offence is not ok.


Hope to see/meet you very soon!
name: Copenhagen Hard Rock & Heavy Metal Meetup

description:
This is a group for people who love to go to live concerts with the bands they love with friends and strangers, and for those who want to discover new bands.

It is managed by Low-Fi, a community for user-generated, intimate live gigs. BUT, we don’t want this group to be just an advertising board for Low-Fi. We really want to support live music in general and we want people to continue to schedule meetups around love music.

So, if you want to post a gig, just write Low-Fi (Co-organizer) and ask to be made an event organizer. We welcome any live music experience in and around Copenhagen.

Let's music2gether!

category.name: music
description:
Welcome to Musicians in Copenhagen.

This group is intended for use for musicians in Copenhagen and surrounding areas.
If you wish to get in contact or arrange meetups with group members, please propose a meetup, and we will make it public, and help you facilitate the arrangement, and perhaps find a place for the meetup to take place.

We keep this group alive to make it possible for the members to make arrangements and meetups. Do not expect us to do the work, it is entirely up to you to make things happen :-)

So if you have an idea for an arrangment to educate or entertain other people, please step forward.

Kind regards,
Per Butschkow

description:
I thought it could be nice to have a way to connect with classical music enthusiasts in Copenhagen. We could meet privately and play each other our favorites. Go to concerts. If there's an event you'd like to go to and gather some company to join you please don't hesitate to shoot me a PM and I'll create it for you so that you can administer it. Sadly Meetup has removed the ability for casual members to create events.

category.name: music
description: It has been claimed that Opera will disappear but it is much more alive today than most of people believe. Those who are aware of its magnificent aesthetic experience are more than welcome to join this journey that will make us forget daily life while letting our most inner emotions to dance, boil, melt or fly together. We will join opera lovers and we will meet two times every month.  In the first meeting (of every month) we will talk about general and contextual information of a selected opera and then we will appreciate the first half of the opera (if the opera is not too long we can watch the full opera the same day). During the second meeting (of every month) we will continue appreciating the second half of the opera and at the end we can share ideas about how was the opera for everyone and what opera should be the next one. During the meetings we can find time to fika and know each one of the members !!!  We can also plan to go to live operas in Stockholm.... It will be super fun !!!

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup
organizer.name: Ulrika W

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. This is not an introduction to Ableton Live or to music making, but you do not need to be a pro. You might want to practice doing some live looping in advance of the meet - doesn't need to be anything fancy, just know how to do it.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup
organizer.name: Ulrika W

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. category.name: music
description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup
organizer.name: Ulrika W

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: It has been claimed that Opera will disappear but it is much more alive today than most of people believe. Those who are aware of its magnificent aesthetic experience are more than welcome to join this journey that will make us forget daily life while letting our most inner emotions to dance, boil, melt or fly together. We will join opera lovers and we will meet two times every month.  In the first meeting (of every month) we will talk about general and contextual information of a selected opera and then we will appreciate the first half of the opera (if the opera is not too long we can watch the full opera the same day). During the second meeting (of every month) we will continue appreciating the second half of the opera and at the end we can share ideas about how was the opera for everyone and what opera should be the next one. During the meetings we can find time to fika and know each one of the members !!!  We can also plan to go to live operas in Stockholm.... It will be super fun !!!
name: Uppsala Opera appreciation in context

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. It's recommended to create an Ableton project with at least one set and have all of your MIDI and sound routings, your favorite sounds, synths, audio and MIDI clips, effects, Max 4 Live devices, etc. ready to go. This is not an introduction to Ableton Live or to music making, but you do not need to be a pro. You might want to practice doing some live looping in advance of the meet - doesn't need to be anything fancy, just know how to do it.

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup
organizer.name: Ulrika W

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

Let's music2gether!

description:
Welcome to Musicians in Copenhagen.

This group is intended for use for musicians in Copenhagen and surrounding areas.
If you wish to get in contact or arrange meetups with group members, please propose a meetup, and we will make it public, and help you facilitate the arrangement, and perhaps find a place for the meetup to take place.

We keep this group alive to make it possible for the members to make arrangements and meetups. Do not expect us to do the work, it is entirely up to you to make things happen :-)

So if you have an idea for an arrangment to educate or entertain other people, please step forward.

Kind regards,
Per Butschkow

description:
Working with document management, ECM, process management, records management, archives, automation of processes? Then this is for you! We will meet and talk about ECM and related topics.

Vi mødes og taler om stort og småt, deler erfaringer og viden og lærer hinanden at kende. Hvis der ikke er plads nok, så finder vi et større sted til næste gang.

Vi taler om teknologier, metoder, værktøjer, best practices, læser rapporter m.m.

Vi har en gruppe hvor vi taler om forskellige emner vi ønsker at tage op på vores fysiske Meetup's: https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12014816

category.name: music
description:
Indie CPH is a Meetup group for anyone into Indie and alternative music, past, present, and future. We do gig meetups, listening parties, record store crawls, and any other ideas we may come up with.

What's Indie then? Indie is both a label as in "music that is independently produced outside of a major record label", but also a genre associated with bands like Blur, The Strokes, The Libertines, Belle and Sebastian etc. We do like to keep the definition broad, but we're probably not metal, stadium rock, world music, jazz and so on.

So join us and discover new and old indie music, find gig buddies, and join our upcoming events!

We're also on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/groups/IndieCPH/

category.name: music
description:
This is a group for all rock and metal listeners in Copenhagen (and the surroundings), who want to meet other metalheads. Whether you like the riffs in trash metal, fantasy in power metal, paganism in folk metal, growls of death metal or shrieks of black metal you are welcome to join us.

*Please take 2 minutes to read the following, so you can get the best out of this group.

About our group

We are a super easy-going bunch of people – both Danes and internationals – who love to listen to and/or play heavier music (metal, rock, punk and everything in between) and just want to help connect those in Copenhagen & its surroundings with new friends and introduce them to different bands, genres and venues. We love live music, jamming, and going down the pub to chat (with or without drinks: your call). If you haven’t been to one of our events yet, you totally should. We’re not that scary, honest.

Attendance policy

We understand that life happens and things change, but please try and let us know if you’ve signed up to an event but won’t make it. Otherwise we might spend the entire night worrying about you.

Serial offenders will be marked as non-attendees, just so that our hard-working hosts know not to spend too much time waiting for/contacting them.

As Jesus once said: 'Thou shalt not RSVP Yes on Meetup and then stay at home in thine pyjamas watching Netflix without letting me know, or I cannot promise to save thy soul.'

Events

Most of our meetups are created by the organisers, but we strongly encourage all members to be active and suggest events.
You can do so by writing to one of the organisers, or starting a discussion (see group's main page).
So if you’re a concert-freak and always up-to-date with all the metal events in the area, your knowledge will definitely be useful to us!
Or if you decide to go to a concert and would like to meet other people who share your taste in bands, we can create an event for you. In that case, you'll have the responsibility of being a ‘host’. It’s not as hard as it sounds. You just have to choose a meeting place/time and make sure that the attendees are aware of it by writing private messages and/or comments in the event page.

And you can also suggest events in the Facebook group, but mind that not all the people from meetup are members of the FB group, so you'd reach more people by starting a new discussion on meetup.

The Facebook group

Yeah, we have one of those. Find it here: https://www.facebook.com/groups/254082381762001/

We use it to float ideas about possible events, new venues, or just to see if anyone is up for going out or playing some music together. Join it, use it, invite your friends. Interaction is the key to new connections (but remember to stick to the rules…)

Group rules

(TL;DR – Don’t provoke unnecessarily, but also don’t be a massive snowflake.)

This should be self-explanatory to anyone accustomed to conducting themselves in society, but let’s set it out in writing anyway.

Just be excellent to each other. Respect the diverse range of nationalities, personalities and music tastes represented in the group.

Unacceptable behaviour includes, but is not limited to:

Racism, Sexism, Ageism, Classism, Ableism, Genreism, Jism,

Homophobia, Xenophobia

Making people feel in any way uncomfortable

Trolling, Shameless advertising, Causing avoidable arguments, Not taking a joke

NB. Swearing is allowed, otherwise we would have to kick ourselves out of the group, but swearing with the intent of causing offence is not ok.


Hope to see/meet you very soon!

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer

description:
This is a group for people who love to go to live concerts with the bands they love with friends and strangers, and for those who want to discover new bands.

It is managed by Low-Fi, a community for user-generated, intimate live gigs. BUT, we don’t want this group to be just an advertising board for Low-Fi. We really want to support live music in general and we want people to continue to schedule meetups around love music.

So, if you want to post a gig, just write Low-Fi (Co-organizer) and ask to be made an event organizer. We welcome any live music experience in and around Copenhagen.

Let's music2gether!

description:
Welcome to Musicians in Copenhagen.

This group is intended for use for musicians in Copenhagen and surrounding areas.
If you wish to get in contact or arrange meetups with group members, please propose a meetup, and we will make it public, and help you facilitate the arrangement, and perhaps find a place for the meetup to take place.

We keep this group alive to make it possible for the members to make arrangements and meetups. Do not expect us to do the work, it is entirely up to you to make things happen :-)

So if you have an idea for an arrangment to educate or entertain other people, please step forward.

Kind regards,
Per Butschkow
name: Musicians in Copenhagen

description:
Working with document management, ECM, process management, records management, archives, automation of processes? Then this is for you! We will meet and talk about ECM and related topics.

We'll talk about technologies, best practices, review reports and much more.

All is welcome - both vendors and users.

Don't speak Danish? No problem, we all speak pretty good English!

We have a group on LinkedIn, where we talk about topics for the coming Meetup: https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12014816


In Danish: Arbejder du med digitalisering, ECM, elektronisk dokumenthåndtering, ESDH, digitalisering og automatisering af arbejdsgange? Så er dette lige noget for dig! 

Vi mødes og taler om stort og småt, deler erfaringer og viden og lærer hinanden at kende. Hvis der ikke er plads nok, så finder vi et større sted til næste gang.

Vi taler om teknologier, metoder, værktøjer, best practices, læser rapporter m.m.

Vi har en gruppe hvor vi taler om forskellige emner vi ønsker at tage op på vores fysiske Meetup's: https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12014816

description:
Indie CPH is a Meetup group for anyone into Indie and alternative music, past, present, and future. We do gig meetups, listening parties, record store crawls, and any other ideas we may come up with.

What's Indie then? Indie is both a label as in "music that is independently produced outside of a major record label", but also a genre associated with bands like Blur, The Strokes, The Libertines, Belle and Sebastian etc. We do like to keep the definition broad, but we're probably not metal, stadium rock, world music, jazz and so on.

So join us and discover new and old indie music, find gig buddies, and join our upcoming events!

We're also on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/groups/IndieCPH/

category.name: music
description:
This is a group for all rock and metal listeners in Copenhagen (and the surroundings), who want to meet other metalheads. Whether you like the riffs in trash metal, fantasy in power metal, paganism in folk metal, growls of death metal or shrieks of black metal you are welcome to join us.

*Please take 2 minutes to read the following, so you can get the best out of this group.

About our group

We are a super easy-going bunch of people – both Danes and internationals – who love to listen to and/or play heavier music (metal, rock, punk and everything in between) and just want to help connect those in Copenhagen & its surroundings with new friends and introduce them to different bands, genres and venues. We love live music, jamming, and going down the pub to chat (with or without drinks: your call). If you haven’t been to one of our events yet, you totally should. We’re not that scary, honest.

Attendance policy

We understand that life happens and things change, but please try and let us know if you’ve signed up to an event but won’t make it. Otherwise we might spend the entire night worrying about you.

Serial offenders will be marked as non-attendees, just so that our hard-working hosts know not to spend too much time waiting for/contacting them.

As Jesus once said: 'Thou shalt not RSVP Yes on Meetup and then stay at home in thine pyjamas watching Netflix without letting me know, or I cannot promise to save thy soul.'

Events

Most of our meetups are created by the organisers, but we strongly encourage all members to be active and suggest events.
You can do so by writing to one of the organisers, or starting a discussion (see group's main page).
So if you’re a concert-freak and always up-to-date with all the metal events in the area, your knowledge will definitely be useful to us!
Or if you decide to go to a concert and would like to meet other people who share your taste in bands, we can create an event for you. In that case, you'll have the responsibility of being a ‘host’. It’s not as hard as it sounds. You just have to choose a meeting place/time and make sure that the attendees are aware of it by writing private messages and/or comments in the event page.

And you can also suggest events in the Facebook group, but mind that not all the people from meetup are members of the FB group, so you'd reach more people by starting a new discussion on meetup.

The Facebook group

Yeah, we have one of those. Find it here: https://www.facebook.com/groups/254082381762001/

We use it to float ideas about possible events, new venues, or just to see if anyone is up for going out or playing some music together. Join it, use it, invite your friends. Interaction is the key to new connections (but remember to stick to the rules…)

Group rules

(TL;DR – Don’t provoke unnecessarily, but also don’t be a massive snowflake.)

This should be self-explanatory to anyone accustomed to conducting themselves in society, but let’s set it out in writing anyway.

Just be excellent to each other. Respect the diverse range of nationalities, personalities and music tastes represented in the group.

Unacceptable behaviour includes, but is not limited to:

Racism, Sexism, Ageism, Classism, Ableism, Genreism, Jism,

Homophobia, Xenophobia

Making people feel in any way uncomfortable

Trolling, Shameless advertising, Causing avoidable arguments, Not taking a joke

NB. Swearing is allowed, otherwise we would have to kick ourselves out of the group, but swearing with the intent of causing offence is not ok.


Hope to see/meet you very soon!
name: Copenhagen Hard Rock & Heavy Metal Meetup

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup
organizer.name: Ulrika W

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: It has been claimed that Opera will disappear but it is much more alive today than most of people believe. Those who are aware of its magnificent aesthetic experience are more than welcome to join this journey that will make us forget daily life while letting our most inner emotions to dance, boil, melt or fly together. We will join opera lovers and we will meet two times every month.  In the first meeting (of every month) we will talk about general and contextual information of a selected opera and then we will appreciate the first half of the opera (if the opera is not too long we can watch the full opera the same day). During the second meeting (of every month) we will continue appreciating the second half of the opera and at the end we can share ideas about how was the opera for everyone and what opera should be the next one. During the meetings we can find time to fika and know each one of the members !!!  We can also plan to go to live operas in Stockholm.... It will be super fun !!!
name: Uppsala Opera appreciation in context

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. It's recommended to create an Ableton project with at least one set and have all of your MIDI and sound routings, your favorite sounds, synths, audio and MIDI clips, effects, Max 4 Live devices, etc. ready to go. This is not an introduction to Ableton Live or to music making, but you do not need to be a pro. You might want to practice doing some live looping in advance of the meet - doesn't need to be anything fancy, just know how to do it.

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.
name: Stockholm Music Industry

Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description: It has been claimed that Opera will disappear but it is much more alive today than most of people believe. Those who are aware of its magnificent aesthetic experience are more than welcome to join this journey that will make us forget daily life while letting our most inner emotions to dance, boil, melt or fly together. We will join opera lovers and we will meet two times every month.  In the first meeting (of every month) we will talk about general and contextual information of a selected opera and then we will appreciate the first half of the opera (if the opera is not too long we can watch the full opera the same day). During the second meeting (of every month) we will continue appreciating the second half of the opera and at the end we can share ideas about how was the opera for everyone and what opera should be the next one. During the meetings we can find time to fika and know each one of the members !!!  We can also plan to go to live operas in Stockholm.... It will be super fun !!!
name: Uppsala Opera appreciation in context

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. It's recommended to create an Ableton project with at least one set and have all of your MIDI and sound routings, your favorite sounds, synths, audio and MIDI clips, effects, Max 4 Live devices, etc. ready to go. This is not an introduction to Ableton Live or to music making, but you do not need to be a pro. You might want to practice doing some live looping in advance of the meet - doesn't need to be anything fancy, just know how to do it.

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: It has been claimed that Opera will disappear but it is much more alive today than most of people believe. Those who are aware of its magnificent aesthetic experience are more than welcome to join this journey that will make us forget daily life while letting our most inner emotions to dance, boil, melt or fly together. We will join opera lovers and we will meet two times every month.  In the first meeting (of every month) we will talk about general and contextual information of a selected opera and then we will appreciate the first half of the opera (if the opera is not too long we can watch the full opera the same day). During the second meeting (of every month) we will continue appreciating the second half of the opera and at the end we can share ideas about how was the opera for everyone and what opera should be the next one. During the meetings we can find time to fika and know each one of the members !!!  We can also plan to go to live operas in Stockholm.... It will be super fun !!!
name: Uppsala Opera appreciation in context

category.name: music
description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: The Stockholm Music Industry group is for musicians, producers, managers, record labels, agents, music supervisors, etc - to meet, collaborate, create events, launch new recording projects, share promotion ideas, and simply grow the music business in Stockholm. My name is Peter Fosso. Much of my life I've spent as a musician and entrepreneur. I'm the founder of Global Music Project.org, the non-profit organization that helps music fans discover independent artists from around the world while it helps support its music preservation mission. I hope you can visit the site, create a profile, and donate your music or make a financial contribution. In addition to my work with Global Music Project, I'm now the head of development for Music2Deal.com in the United States. Music2Deal is the definitive online networking site for the music industry, helping managers, booking agents, producers, music supervisors, artists and other music industry professionals promote their songs, artists, and businesses to thousands of Music2Deal members in over 30 different countries. Join this great Meetup and come meet some fellow music professionals.

category.name: music
description:
Do you like Nordic folk music and want to hang out with nice, easy going people? Whether you are new to Stockholm, just visiting or have been living here all your life, you’re welcome to this community to meet new people, talk, play music, sing, dance and learn from each other in a relaxed non-prestigious way.

In an old building in the center of Stockholm- “Skeppis”- there are all join-in folk songs, music instructions, dance instructions, children´s dance and music jams in various rooms open for everyone, whatever level, age, gender or nationality. From 20.00 and onwards there is also an open dance floor for up to 150 people. Skeppis is open every Sunday free of charge. In the café, which also is a music jam nest, you get dinner (soup with a sandwich) for less than 50 sek. Everything is run by volunteers, from the kitchen to the instructions and if you like it you can give a donation to the café to keep it all running. The whole house is an alcohol- and smoke free area. See the link below for more information about the instructions. Within an hour from Stockholm there are also plenty of other events for folk music jams, dance and concerts. Bring your instrument and/or dance shoes and tell your friends here on Meetup when you´re going! Skeppis: http://www.folkmusikhuset.se/en/
name: Stockholm Folk Music Meetup
organizer.name: Ulrika W

category.name: music
description:
I've been creating some sorts of "soundscapes", almost as psychedelic country/folk but not... harmonic riffs and vamps held up by atmospheric slide guitar, mandolin, upright bass (a cello, actually)...I want to move in the direction of a Sigur Ros, Tom Waits, Moondog, Nick Cave (recent albums), Phillip Glass kinda thing.
I want to meet any and all musicians... if you play, and want to create something beautiful and undefinable, let me know. I'd really love to find a piano/keyboard player that could lay down some solid roots to what I'm playing and help me move into new directions... would love a sax player or 2, clarinet (bass clarinet! but regular is great, too), violin, someone that can double/triple on any stringed instrument (bass, guitar, mandolin). A sitar would be useful. Any guitar players that write sad, melancholic, exotic shit.
Really need some vocalists a la Cocteau Twins, Nick Cave, Dylan, Tom Waits, The Cranes, Velevet Underground, Kate Bush. Let's just be nuts and see what happens.
Check me out on soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/mageever-believer
name: Looking for musicians to complete my ideal project Stockholm

description: Ableton laptop jams at our studio space in Kungsholmen. Bring your laptop, audio interface, cables, and optionally a controller or two. We provide the venue and the amplification. This is not an introduction to Ableton Live or to music making, but you do not need to be a pro. description:
This is a group for people who love to go to live concerts with the bands they love with friends and strangers, and for those who want to discover new bands.

It is managed by Low-Fi, a community for user-generated, intimate live gigs. BUT, we don’t want this group to be just an advertising board for Low-Fi. We really want to support live music in general and we want people to continue to schedule meetups around love music.

So, if you want to post a gig, just write Low-Fi (Co-organizer) and ask to be made an event organizer. We welcome any live music experience in and around Copenhagen.

Let's music2gether!

category.name: music
description:
Welcome to Musicians in Copenhagen.

This group is intended for use for musicians in Copenhagen and surrounding areas.
If you wish to get in contact or arrange meetups with group members, please propose a meetup, and we will make it public, and help you facilitate the arrangement, and perhaps find a place for the meetup to take place.

We keep this group alive to make it possible for the members to make arrangements and meetups. Do not expect us to do the work, it is entirely up to you to make things happen :-)

So if you have an idea for an arrangment to educate or entertain other people, please step forward.

Kind regards,
Per Butschkow

category.name: music
description:
I thought it could be nice to have a way to connect with classical music enthusiasts in Copenhagen. We could meet privately and play each other our favorites. Go to concerts. Have heated debates about who did the best recordings. Maybe have a glass of wine. Expand our classical music horizons. Or maybe just start looking at it - every interested person is welcome! Suggestions are very welcome too! 

If there's an event you'd like to go to and gather some company to join you please don't hesitate to shoot me a PM and I'll create it for you so that you can administer it. Sadly Meetup has removed the ability for casual members to create events.

description:
Working with document management, ECM, process management, records management, archives, automation of processes? Then this is for you! We will meet and talk about ECM and related topics.

We'll talk about technologies, best practices, review reports and much more.

All is welcome - both vendors and users.

Don't speak Danish? No problem, we all speak pretty good English!

We have a group on LinkedIn, where we talk about topics for the coming Meetup: https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12014816


In Danish: Arbejder du med digitalisering, ECM, elektronisk dokumenthåndtering, ESDH, digitalisering og automatisering af arbejdsgange? Så er dette lige noget for dig! 

Vi mødes og taler om stort og småt, deler erfaringer og viden og lærer hinanden at kende. Hvis der ikke er plads nok, så finder vi et større sted til næste gang.

Vi taler om teknologier, metoder, værktøjer, best practices, læser rapporter m.m.

Vi har en gruppe hvor vi taler om forskellige emner vi ønsker at tage op på vores fysiske Meetup's: https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12014816

category.name: music
description:
Indie CPH is a Meetup group for anyone into Indie and alternative music, past, present, and future. We do gig meetups, listening parties, record store crawls, and any other ideas we may come up with.

What's Indie then? Indie is both a label as in "music that is independently produced outside of a major record label", but also a genre associated with bands like Blur, The Strokes, The Libertines, Belle and Sebastian etc. We do like to keep the definition broad, but we're probably not metal, stadium rock, world music, jazz and so on.

So join us and discover new and old indie music, find gig buddies, and join our upcoming events!

We're also on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/groups/IndieCPH/

category.name: music
description:
This is a group for all rock and metal listeners in Copenhagen (and the surroundings), who want to meet other metalheads. Whether you like the riffs in trash metal, fantasy in power metal, paganism in folk metal, growls of death metal or shrieks of black metal you are welcome to join us.

*Please take 2 minutes to read the following, so you can get the best out of this group.

About our group

We are a super easy-going bunch of people – both Danes and internationals – who love to listen to and/or play heavier music (metal, rock, punk and everything in between) and just want to help connect those in Copenhagen & its surroundings with new friends and introduce them to different bands, genres and venues. We love live music, jamming, and going down the pub to chat (with or without drinks: your call). If you haven’t been to one of our events yet, you totally should. We’re not that scary, honest.

Attendance policy

We understand that life happens and things change, but please try and let us know if you’ve signed up to an event but won’t make it. Otherwise we might spend the entire night worrying about you.

Serial offenders will be marked as non-attendees, just so that our hard-working hosts know not to spend too much time waiting for/contacting them.

As Jesus once said: 'Thou shalt not RSVP Yes on Meetup and then stay at home in thine pyjamas watching Netflix without letting me know, or I cannot promise to save thy soul.'

Events

Most of our meetups are created by the organisers, but we strongly encourage all members to be active and suggest events.
You can do so by writing to one of the organisers, or starting a discussion (see group's main page).
So if you’re a concert-freak and always up-to-date with all the metal events in the area, your knowledge will definitely be useful to us!
Or if you decide to go to a concert and would like to meet other people who share your taste in bands, we can create an event for you. In that case, you'll have the responsibility of being a ‘host’. It’s not as hard as it sounds. You just have to choose a meeting place/time and make sure that the attendees are aware of it by writing private messages and/or comments in the event page.

And you can also suggest events in the Facebook group, but mind that not all the people from meetup are members of the FB group, so you'd reach more people by starting a new discussion on meetup.

The Facebook group

Yeah, we have one of those. Find it here: https://www.facebook.com/groups/254082381762001/

We use it to float ideas about possible events, new venues, or just to see if anyone is up for going out or playing some music together. Join it, use it, invite your friends. Interaction is the key to new connections (but remember to stick to the rules…)

Group rules

(TL;DR – Don’t provoke unnecessarily, but also don’t be a massive snowflake.)

This should be self-explanatory to anyone accustomed to conducting themselves in society, but let’s set it out in writing anyway.

Just be excellent to each other. Respect the diverse range of nationalities, personalities and music tastes represented in the group.

Unacceptable behaviour includes, but is not limited to:

Racism, Sexism, Ageism, Classism, Ableism, Genreism, Jism,

Homophobia, Xenophobia

Making people feel in any way uncomfortable

Trolling, Shameless advertising, Causing avoidable arguments, Not taking a joke

NB. Swearing is allowed, otherwise we would have to kick ourselves out of the group, but swearing with the intent of causing offence is not ok.


Hope to see/meet you very soon!
